Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.66,0:00:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for disturbing you so early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.95,0:00:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're from the county police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.84,0:00:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.34,0:00:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for asking, but have you been here all night?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.22,0:00:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, I was out drinking until morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.59,0:00:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.55,0:00:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is that Director Heinemann, Surgical Director \N Oppenheim, and Dr. Boyer of Eisler Memorial Hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.52,0:00:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have all passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we can't let anyone besides \N the police enter the crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:25.95,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(350,319)\fad(300,133)}A Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.68,0:02:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that'll hinder the management of the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.93,0:02:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, no media inside the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.97,0:02:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please refrain from disturbing the patients!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.06,0:02:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So was it an accident, or murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three people died at the same time.  Of course there's something behind it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.40,0:02:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you part of the hospital staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.03,0:02:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any information regarding this incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.65,0:02:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.66,0:02:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me through!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's allowed to enter!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.78,0:02:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a doctor here, Kenzou Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.04,0:02:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.41,0:02:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you see anybody suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait.  This is not the time to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.63,0:02:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma, the director and the others are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.69,0:02:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.65,0:03:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are the emergency cases under control?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.65,0:03:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Thing this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.11,0:03:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're swamped with emergency cases right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, two patients are \N waiting to be operated on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.74,0:03:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll help out too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take care of the car accident \N victim with the head contusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.08,0:03:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll look over his pictures in the X-Ray room first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.13,0:03:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the other case?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.15,0:03:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The patient suffered a stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.17,0:03:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask for your cooperation in the investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.67,0:03:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the time for that right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.34,0:03:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, but the initial investigation \N is the most crucial part of the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.47,0:03:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know anyone who holds a grudge \N against the director and the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.77,0:03:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A grudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The path of being the doctor you \N dreamed of is closed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.28,0:03:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... no.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.95,0:03:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.64,0:03:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't find them anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the sister's bed also empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.59,0:04:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already checked!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.59,0:04:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't find her anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.02,0:04:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell... happened here...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.48,0:04:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He reached out to offer people the hand of salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will commend his lifetime \N achievements for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell, Dr. Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.83,0:04:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May you rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.87,0:04:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.09,0:04:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's hard, but pull yourself together...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.51,0:04:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.47,0:04:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unbearable, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.24,0:05:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.41,0:05:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She led an easy life as the daughter of a director.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.03,0:05:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, she's suddenly just a normal person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be a pretty big shock for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.96,0:05:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you say that at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.08,0:05:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Dr. Tenma, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.50,0:05:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Inspector Weissbach from the Nordrhein-Westfalen \N Police Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for all your efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have my deepest condolences.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:38.31,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(331,445)\fad(200,120)}Inspector Lunge
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:38.31,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(309,360)\fad(200,120)}Bundeskriminalamt
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm inspector Lunge from the BKA
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.33,0:05:38.16,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: The Bundeskriminalamt (BKA) is the German Federal Police, the German FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.89,0:05:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard rumors of the genius doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.52,0:05:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm still young and inexperienced...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm.. you still don't have any leads as \N to whereabouts of the children?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.68,0:05:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but we've discovered the cause of \N death of the director and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.37,0:06:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've extracted a small amount \N of nitric acid from their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.79,0:06:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nitric acid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean a muscle relaxant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.55,0:06:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected from a doctor, you're very familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did something like that end up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same candy wrappers were found beside each body...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.18,0:06:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the same substance was found \N in each of their stomachs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.52,0:06:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, do you have any ideas where \N the three obtained the candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.24,0:06:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, how is the investigation of the twins progressing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.28,0:06:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jurisdiction on the investigation has been \N passed down to us from the local police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.62,0:06:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.17,0:06:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we work back from this incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.46,0:06:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we might find that it all leads to the moment of \N the twins' parents were shot and killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.46,0:06:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After fleeing East Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.15,0:06:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...their parents were shot, and the hospital \N staff that treated were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.06,0:06:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's a chance that it was a political terrorism.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those children may hold a huge key to this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please find them somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give it our best effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.48,0:07:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Japanese doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who was removed form his position \N as chief by the director...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.74,0:07:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and had his engagement to the director's daughter \N canceled right before the incident, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that man has an alibi, since he was drinking \N at a pub at the time the crime was committed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, may I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.13,0:07:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does your hand move like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.35,0:07:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hitting the keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm inputting all the information into the disk in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.56,0:07:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I hit the keys to retrieve the information...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No, I'm still young and inexperienced."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma was blushing and didn't know what \N to say when I called him a genius doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspectors, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you're not a suspect for the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they do have evidence that implicates \N me, so it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were bugging me with questions, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.51,0:08:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel tired for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.76,0:08:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this case cools off...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm thinking of going back to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came all the way to Germany intent \N on doing some research, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...thanks to this string of incidents...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I think I've realized that the primary \N job of a doctor is to save lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.82,0:08:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't say something sad like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.11,0:08:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So very tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.37,0:08:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your progress looks excellent, Mr. Buchner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.75,0:08:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.92,0:08:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will I be able to work again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.05,0:09:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My store will be forced to close if I'm not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you mustn't push yourself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop by for a few drinks once you've been discharged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I can check to see if you're overworking yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.56,0:09:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.11,0:09:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.11,0:09:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are the rumors about you leaving the hospital true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.95,0:09:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any other good doctors like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.83,0:09:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't say that you're quitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.62,0:09:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Buchner...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma, the board chairman is calling for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.63,0:09:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, they're holding a conference \N regarding the personnel reorganization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.28,0:09:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until now, the director's faction has always decided the major appointments...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so I think there's going to be \N a fairly big staff cleanup soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.02,0:09:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it that Dr. Eckener is being \N sent to a small hospital in Bayern...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.11,0:09:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.98,0:09:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please try your best, no matter \N what the chairman says to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.57,0:10:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be cheering for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't leave the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place merit on talent and ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.80,0:10:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.30,0:10:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm appointing you as the head of the surgical department.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.39,0:10:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a life!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After disobeying the director's orders...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...being removed from my place as chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.98,0:10:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...having my engagement to Eva canceled...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.61,0:10:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and choosing a path as a normal doctor, not caring abut promotions or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.83,0:10:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.63,0:10:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a life!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for calling you out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.98,0:11:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you were appointed as the \N head of the surgical department.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.90,0:11:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.77,0:11:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.48,0:11:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzou, at my father's funeral...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you tried to comfort me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.74,0:11:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of things happened between \N us, but I want to start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzou?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.34,0:11:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.22,0:11:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.81,0:11:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to start over!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.81,0:11:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzou...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.09,0:12:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the patient with the spinal cord tumor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.91,0:12:06.95,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(361,271)\fad(304)}Nine Years Later
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.39,0:12:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His paralysis suddenly took a turn for the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do the operation myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.42,0:12:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you, doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.86,0:12:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.78,0:12:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.10,0:12:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, when will this flood recede?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:31.39,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(367,348)\fad(300,100)}Köln, \N Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.82,0:12:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the world would change \N once the Berlin Wall fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.11,0:12:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but nothing good ever happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They talk about the unification of Europe...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but all that floats down here are piles of crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.33,0:12:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the rate of unsolved crimes keeps rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.42,0:12:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, we're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.01,0:12:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of their bodies had their throats cut with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.51,0:12:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their identities?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Reichmann couple that lived on Stich Drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.47,0:12:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were killed in their apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.06,0:13:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We believe they were hidden in a closet, but \N were washed out because of the flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.15,0:13:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another middle-aged couple murder case...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.69,0:13:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the past two years, there have been \N four other cases across Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.82,0:13:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...all done in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.82,0:13:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably just a thief going after \N wealthy middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.95,0:13:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's too early to dismiss these as simple robberies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.33,0:13:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, according to the data, none of the couples had any kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.13,0:13:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, this couple didn't have children, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.13,0:13:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think that assuming it's just \N a robbery is a bit short-sighted?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.59,0:13:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But all the victims had their valuables taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, the amount taken was minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.81,0:13:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, it would make sense if this was the work of a single person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.23,0:13:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying that it wasn't \N the work of a single person?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.15,0:13:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were two incidents that occurred \N inside locked houses with alarms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.99,0:13:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the perpetrator bypassed them easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.37,0:14:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And none of the couples showed any signs \N of struggles before they were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.12,0:14:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, the neighbors, didn't hear a single \N sound during the time of the murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.46,0:14:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's a bit too well-executed \N to be a solo job?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.63,0:14:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.38,0:14:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you familiar with this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.17,0:14:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.11,0:14:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adolf Junkers, 23 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.93,0:14:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrested twice on suspicion of theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.68,0:14:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His specialty is picking locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.35,0:14:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, a so called locksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.14,0:14:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the previous middle aged couple murder cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.87,0:14:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he was spotted near three separate crimes scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.02,0:14:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he's the one who...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.40,0:14:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.28,0:14:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either, way this is all you local police need to do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.74,0:14:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the rest to the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.78,0:14:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I guess it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.16,0:14:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never flown a kite before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.76,0:14:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.47,0:14:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how was the girl last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.43,0:14:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.77,0:15:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey.  She's the director's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.46,0:15:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you just left after dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.98,0:15:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I received an emergency call during dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.03,0:15:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and was called back to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.57,0:15:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, you have to forget this "work \N is number one" ideology!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.16,0:15:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna regret it when you \N let a fine girl slip past you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.41,0:15:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey are you listening to me, doctor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.54,0:15:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flying a kite, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.58,0:15:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.50,0:15:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this yours, Karl?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.92,0:15:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My grandfather gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it just won't fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.18,0:15:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the center is misaligned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how to fly a kite, doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.43,0:15:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to fly them a lot when I as a child in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.52,0:15:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try raising it higher, Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.69,0:15:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.99,0:15:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope this works...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.42,0:16:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.59,0:16:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.42,0:16:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.88,0:16:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were in his position, I'd have at least five lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.68,0:16:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.97,0:16:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Dr. Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.19,0:16:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should try your best to get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.94,0:16:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, you're going to fly it yourself.  Okay, Karl?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.19,0:16:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's operation will be a parasellar \N meningioma extirpation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going with the right pterional approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.87,0:16:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.08,0:16:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.04,0:16:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an operation done by the chief \N surgeon himself, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.38,0:16:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an amazing operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.40,0:16:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The brain is barely retracting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.01,0:16:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is a genius neurosurgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.51,0:16:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You resident doctors should treat the brain with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.06,0:17:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.22,0:17:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.27,0:17:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ambulance! Somebody call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.93,0:17:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.83,0:17:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.65,0:17:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This man just jumped into the street!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.69,0:17:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.91,0:17:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.03,0:17:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's his current condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.12,0:18:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we can't really do anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.49,0:18:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's an important witness in a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.21,0:18:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on his testimony, we may \N be able to solve a serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.48,0:18:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have him die on us like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the patient in in critical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.20,0:18:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do anything at our hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.18,0:18:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best neurosurgeon is at Eisler Memorial Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he comes here, then maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.39,0:18:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A neurosurgeon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.81,0:18:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to have you come all \N the way out here, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.45,0:18:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the patient's condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.37,0:18:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's currently in a state of delirium.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of his pupils is dilated, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.50,0:18:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but who are you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.92,0:18:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.71,0:18:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't met since the director's funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.88,0:18:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're from the BKA...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.68,0:19:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please perform a successful operation \N for the sake of the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.85,0:19:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The patient must live in order \N for us to solve a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.86,0:19:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not operating on him for the sake of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I operate for the sake of the patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.44,0:19:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I have an operation to conduct, so please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.49,0:19:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you've become the head of the \N surgical department, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.87,0:19:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You rose pretty high.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.67,0:19:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's just amazing, considering your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.71,0:19:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The position of director isn't far off, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.63,0:19:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I still have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.72,0:19:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the murder that took place \N at Eisler Memorial Hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.89,0:19:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the investigation is going rather slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.31,0:19:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only clue we have is the poisoned candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.31,0:19:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From this, we can only determine that \N it was done by an intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:20:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An intellectual crime occurs when there's a connection \N between the victim and the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.91,0:20:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.74,0:20:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.58,0:20:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my line of work, I think about \N this kind of stuff all year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.46,0:20:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, please rest assured....
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.62,0:20:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a single case I've been involved \N with has gone unsolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a single one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to seeing the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.52,0:20:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to open the skull and remove \N the intra-cerebral hematomas.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.44,0:20:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry, the brain herniation will \N advance and the patient will be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.36,0:20:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the murder at Eisler Memorial Hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.49,0:20:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I can see only one person who benefited from the \N incident, no matter how much I think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.83,0:20:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma, you're the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.26,0:21:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming all the way out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.53,0:21:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a problem.  How's the patient doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.47,0:21:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's conscious, but his right pupil is dilated.  The anesthesia is still affecting his left side somewhat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already started to rehab routine, hasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.48,0:21:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His paralysis will eventually wear off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.19,0:21:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is going smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.73,0:21:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also I think some police officers want to talk with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.78,0:21:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but please turn them away for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.24,0:21:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that Lunge person is very persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.24,0:21:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The patient's recovery is top priority right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.71,0:21:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.47,0:21:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers, do you know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.34,0:21:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see this finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.72,0:21:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.68,0:21:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you answer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.44,0:21:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.40,0:22:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.03,0:22:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...nster... coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.74,0:22:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming?  What's coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.45,0:22:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.86,0:22:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.63,0:22:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster?
